"{\"uid\": \"limerickleader.ie-news-national-news-1577282-alert-gardai-issue-important-traffic-alert-ahead-of-homecoming-for-ireland-s-olympic-heroes.html\", \"text\": \"Limerick Live  https://www.limerickleader.ie/section/1195/advertise-with-us  Search  02 Dec 2025  Bringing you live local breaking news, sport, politics, weather & more in Limerick and County Limerick  All the latest breaking local news from Limerick and County Limerick  Keep up to date with the latest sports news  Ryder Cup  Read all the latest Irish news and updates from around Ireland  Find whats happening in and around Limerick and County Limerick  Life Magazines  Enjoy our award winning photos and picture galleries taken in Limerick and County Limerick  Catch up on all the latest business news in Limerick and County Limerick  Read about the latest properties available in Limerick and County Limerick  Enjoy our latest and up to date motoring review and news in Limerick and County Limerick  Limerick and County Limerick Met Eireann Weather Forecast  Recent death notices and obituaries from Limerick and County Limerick  Please allow ads as they help fund our trusted local news content.  Kindly addusto your ad blocker whitelist.  If you want further access to Ireland's best local journalism, consider contributing and/or subscribing to our free daily Newsletter .  Support our mission and join our community now.  To continue reading this article, you can subscribe for as little as \\u20ac0.50 per week which will also give you access to all of our premium content and archived articles!  Alternatively, you can pay \\u20ac0.50 per article, capped at \\u20ac1 per day.  Thank you for supporting Ireland's best local journalism!  Team Ireland athletes (L-R) Ciara McGing, Dean Clancy, Jack Marley and Jude Gallagher during the Paris Olympics closing ceremony|PICTURE: David Fitzgerald/Sportsfile  Reporter:  Ellen Gough  12 Aug 2024 9:17 AM  Email:  news@iconicmedia.ie  An Garda S\\u00edoch\\u00e1na have issued a traffic alert for Dublin city centre ahead of the Team Ireland's Olympic homecoming celebrations this Monday afternoon.  The homecoming celebrations for Team Ireland will be held to honour the athletes and their achievements outside the GPO on O' Connell Street at12.30pm Monday afternoon, August 12.  Thousands are expected to turn out to the free event.  According to a press release from Garda\\u00ed, the following traffic and travel plans will be in place from 10.30am Monday morning.  \\u2022 A road closure on O'Connell Street from 10:30am to 17:30pm will be in operation today\\u2022 A single lane will remain open on O'Connell Street from 5:00am to 10:30am and from 17:30pm to 22:30pm.  Diversions will be also in place in Dublin City centre at the following locations:  \\u2022 Northbound Traffic: Diverted onto Eden Quay - Gardiner Street Lower - Parnell Street\\u2022 Southbound Traffic: Diverted off O'Connell Street onto Cathal Brugha Street. Option to turn onto Marlborough Street or Gardiner Street Lower and onto Eden Quay.  Access to the Arnott's car park is limited during today's event.  The LUAS Green line will be closed on O'Connell Street from 10:30am while the\\u00a0LUAS Red line will be closed from Abbey Street to Jervis Street from 10:30am this Monday.  \\\"Garda\\u00ed will be on duty in Dublin city centre today during the event to assist and direct all attendees to the Team Ireland Homecoming Event,\\\" the press release also said.  \\\"An Garda S\\u00edoch\\u00e1na appreciates the co-operation of all road users during today's homecoming celebrations.\\\"  Related topics:  national  4  To continue reading this article,please subscribe and support local journalism!  Subscribing will allow you access to all of our premium content and archived articles.  To continue reading this article for FREE,please kindly register and/or log in.  Registration is absolutely 100% FREE and will help us personalise your experience on our sites.  You can also sign up to our